1
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,867
Angela!

2
00:00:46,933 --> 00:00:48,733
Mommy's here for you, okay?

3
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:52,433
I will take care of you, dear.

4
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,500
We're going to crash!

5
00:00:54,567 --> 00:00:56,900
Please help us!

6
00:00:56,967 --> 00:00:59,267
Angela!

7
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:03,333
Our daughter
has already come out.

8
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:06,333
Why is it that everyone
I love is leaving me?

9
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:12,367
The only thing that can rid me
of this searing pain...

10
00:01:12,467 --> 00:01:15,967
is if I can be
with Angela again.

11
00:01:16,033 --> 00:01:19,233
We're bringing people
to the evacuation center!

12
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:20,633
Follow us!

13
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:30,667
Danilo!

14
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,333
No. He's not answering.

15
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,033
Maybe he lost the signal.

16
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:38,300
I'm going home! I need to go.

17
00:01:38,367 --> 00:01:39,267
Emma.

18
00:01:39,333 --> 00:01:40,567
What's going on here?

19
00:01:40,667 --> 00:01:42,333
Why are you panicking?

20
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,233
Ma'am, I need to go home.

21
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:46,033
I'm sorry.

22
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:48,133
Emma can't reach her husband.

23
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:50,333
There's a storm brewing
in their area right now.

24
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:53,833
Almost 20 houses were destroyed
by the landslide.

25
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:56,933
A large part of the mountain
slid and collapsed,

26
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,700
here in Barangay Pinagkaisa.

27
00:01:58,767 --> 00:02:00,533
That's our barangay!

28
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:04,100
That's our barangay!

29
00:02:04,167 --> 00:02:08,433
- Emma!
- That's our barangay!

30
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:12,267
- My daughter...
- Emma!

31
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:22,267
Sir, Sir, Sir!

32
00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:24,467
Sir! Slowly.

33
00:02:24,533 --> 00:02:26,700
Where am I?
What am I doing here?

34
00:02:26,767 --> 00:02:28,667
You're in an evacuation center.

35
00:02:28,733 --> 00:02:30,367
You were found
unconscious on the street.

36
00:02:30,433 --> 00:02:31,867
So they brought you here.

37
00:02:31,933 --> 00:02:33,133
What?

38
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,267
Ouch.

39
00:02:34,333 --> 00:02:36,067
You hit your head on the ground.

40
00:02:36,133 --> 00:02:38,733
Good thing it isn't serious.

41
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:41,967
My daughter.
Where's my daughter?

42
00:02:42,033 --> 00:02:44,367
There was no child with you
when you were brought here.

43
00:02:44,433 --> 00:02:45,533
What?

44
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,500
I need to go back
for my daughter.

45
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,600
Sir, hold on! Sir!

46
00:02:49,667 --> 00:02:50,933
Sir, it's still dangerous.

47
00:02:52,167 --> 00:02:55,200
- Sir!
- Don't stop me!

48
00:02:55,267 --> 00:02:56,733
Calm down, Sir. It's dangerous.

49
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,933
I need to go home
and find my daughter!

50
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,567
Dan!

51
00:03:01,633 --> 00:03:05,067
- Don't stop me!
- Dan!

52
00:03:05,133 --> 00:03:06,733
Dan!

53
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:15,900
Where's our daughter?

54
00:03:15,967 --> 00:03:18,100
Where's Kayla?

55
00:03:18,167 --> 00:03:21,133
Why isn't she with you?
Where's Kayla?

56
00:03:21,233 --> 00:03:24,733
She was left in the house, Emma.

57
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:27,233
She was left in the house.

58
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:45,100
Medic! Medic!

59
00:03:45,167 --> 00:03:47,167
Over here!

60
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:06,833
Stretcher! We need it here!

61
00:04:09,067 --> 00:04:10,200
Mister?

62
00:04:10,267 --> 00:04:11,800
Mister, our daughter.

63
00:04:11,867 --> 00:04:12,933
She's under the mud.

64
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,833
Please dig her up.
Please save her!

65
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:17,033
I'm begging you, Mister!

66
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:18,533
We're still waiting
for the backhoe

67
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,067
that we'll use
to dig the ground.

68
00:04:20,133 --> 00:04:22,433
It can't pass through
because the roads are closed.

69
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:24,067
What time will it arrive?

70
00:04:24,133 --> 00:04:26,500
Our daughter is buried there!
What are you going to do?

71
00:04:26,567 --> 00:04:27,633
Are you just going
to stand there?

72
00:04:27,733 --> 00:04:28,633
Ma'am, please calm down.

73
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:29,967
How can I calm down?

74
00:04:30,033 --> 00:04:31,900
My daughter
is buried underneath!

75
00:04:31,967 --> 00:04:33,633
She needs help!

76
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:35,600
I'll do it if you don't!

77
00:04:35,667 --> 00:04:36,867
- You can't...
- Dear!

78
00:04:36,933 --> 00:04:40,133
- Emma!
- My daughter!

79
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:42,367
- Kayla!
- My dear!

80
00:04:42,433 --> 00:04:44,600
Kayla!

81
00:04:44,667 --> 00:04:46,167
Dear!

82
00:04:46,233 --> 00:04:48,200
Kayla, my dear!

83
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:50,467
Kayla! Kayla!

84
00:04:50,533 --> 00:04:53,100
Kayla! Dear!

85
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:54,733
Mom's here!

86
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:57,500
Mom's here!

87
00:04:57,567 --> 00:05:00,767
Hang in there.

88
00:05:00,867 --> 00:05:04,800
Kayla's here!

89
00:05:04,867 --> 00:05:08,733
Find our daughter.

90
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,667
Kayla's here, Dan.

91
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:14,067
I can feel it.

92
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:16,533
Kayla's here!

93
00:05:22,733 --> 00:05:24,167
Dan.

94
00:05:24,233 --> 00:05:27,533
Dan, let's go back for Kayla.

95
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,500
Dan.

96
00:05:28,567 --> 00:05:32,333
It's late now, Emma.

97
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,100
What will happen to our child?

98
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:37,033
Poor baby. She's all alone.

99
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:40,033
I'm sure she's so scared, Dan.

100
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:42,333
Didn't you hear what
the rescue team said?

101
00:05:44,067 --> 00:05:47,400
They will wait
for the backhoe.

102
00:05:47,467 --> 00:05:49,733
What do we do?
Will we just stand here?

103
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:53,500
We don't have the tools
to find Baby Kayla.

104
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:55,233
Don't you want
to find our daughter?

105
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:57,400
Don't you want to?

106
00:05:57,467 --> 00:06:00,167
Of course I do!

107
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:02,500
I'm just worried
for you, Emma.

108
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:04,933
I don't want anything
bad to happen to you!

109
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:09,633
We're talking
about our daughter!

110
00:06:09,733 --> 00:06:13,100
We can't just stand
here and do nothing!

111
00:06:13,167 --> 00:06:15,600
Dan, we once lost Kayla.

112
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:18,733
We can't lose her!

113
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,967
We made a promise,
didn't we?

114
00:06:20,033 --> 00:06:21,800
We made a promise!

115
00:06:21,867 --> 00:06:25,100
We promised we'd do
everything for her!

116
00:06:25,167 --> 00:06:27,933
Are we going to give up now?

117
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,667
What now? Say something!

118
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:32,567
Don't you want
to find Kayla?

119
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,567
Do it your way.

120
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:08,700
Kayla!

121
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:18,733
Kayla!

122
00:07:30,733 --> 00:07:31,967
Mom.

123
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:35,533
Mom, thank you for coming with
us despite the ungodly hour.

124
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,400
Of course.

125
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:40,233
My granddaughter is missing.

126
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:42,167
But don't worry.

127
00:07:42,233 --> 00:07:47,033
We won't stop until we find her.

128
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:49,567
You just have to be strong.

129
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:52,367
Okay.

130
00:07:58,967 --> 00:07:59,900
Dan?

131
00:07:59,967 --> 00:08:01,300
Dan, do you think...

132
00:08:01,367 --> 00:08:05,267
do you think Kayla's there?

133
00:08:05,333 --> 00:08:07,733
I don't think I can
bear to see that.

134
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:10,900
- Mom.
- Wait.

135
00:08:10,967 --> 00:08:12,133
I'll check.

136
00:08:14,167 --> 00:08:16,467
My God, please don't take
Kayla away from us.

137
00:08:16,533 --> 00:08:19,233
Please bring her
back to us alive.

138
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:24,167
Sir, did you find a baby?

139
00:08:24,233 --> 00:08:26,533
Sorry, Sir, but we didn't.

140
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,033
Emma...

141
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:36,400
they didn't find a baby.

142
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:37,833
Nothing?

143
00:08:37,900 --> 00:08:39,033
She's not there?
Does it mean...

144
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:41,967
my granddaughter
is still buried underneath?

145
00:08:42,033 --> 00:08:44,733
- Do something! Find her!
- Dan.

146
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,000
Dan, is Kayla still alive?

147
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:49,667
Do you think Kayla
is still alive?

148
00:08:49,733 --> 00:08:52,133
- I don't know.
- Oh no.

149
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:55,933
If she got buried underneath,
she'd probably be dead by now.

150
00:08:56,033 --> 00:08:57,333
What did you say?

151
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,100
She's probably dead! Dead?

152
00:09:00,167 --> 00:09:02,167
Bastard!

153
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:04,700
You're rude! You disrespect us!

154
00:09:04,767 --> 00:09:07,033
That's enough. Stop!

155
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:09,167
You deserve that! You're crazy!

156
00:09:09,233 --> 00:09:10,733
Crazy!

157
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,800
Let's go. And you,
just ignore that.

158
00:09:12,867 --> 00:09:14,433
We're already
in a difficult situation.

159
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:15,667
What if he files
a complaint?

160
00:09:15,733 --> 00:09:19,367
What will happen? That's going
to be another problem!

161
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:21,933
Where is my granddaughter?

162
00:09:59,967 --> 00:10:02,333
Dear.

163
00:10:02,433 --> 00:10:04,567
Keep this with you, okay?

164
00:10:04,633 --> 00:10:08,733
So you'll remember me
even though I'm far away.

165
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:11,833
Whenever you hold this cloth,

166
00:10:11,900 --> 00:10:16,500
you'll feel that I'm beside you.

167
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:23,500
Kayla!

168
00:10:23,567 --> 00:10:27,167
Dear!

169
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:29,667
Dear!

170
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:36,600
Dear! Kayla!

171
00:10:55,633 --> 00:10:59,333
We can't lose Kayla.

172
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:02,433
I can't lose my daughter!

173
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,433
Why the long face?

174
00:11:08,267 --> 00:11:16,400
We've sold our things so we can
buy Kayla's medicine.

175
00:11:20,733 --> 00:11:21,300
Dear,

176
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:24,833
I found a solution
to your problem.

177
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:29,200
I met a wealthy couple.

178
00:11:29,267 --> 00:11:32,800
They're willing to pay
for Kayla's hospitalization.

179
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:37,600
- Really?
- Yes.

180
00:11:37,667 --> 00:11:39,433
They will pay for everything.

181
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:42,767
As well as raising the child...

182
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:45,800
if you'll give
her up for adoption.

183
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:47,800
Mom.

184
00:11:47,867 --> 00:11:51,133
Dear, you don't have
to worry about anything.

185
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,633
They will raise her.

186
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:53,700
You won't have anything
to worry about.

187
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:55,200
Don't you like that?

188
00:11:55,267 --> 00:12:02,033
Mom, our daughter is not a puppy
you can just give away.

189
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:06,367
You even dare to talk when
you're just a nobody!

190
00:12:06,433 --> 00:12:07,533
I'm not talking to you.

191
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,267
Don't butt in.

192
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,933
Dear,

193
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:17,533
accept my acquaintance's offer.

194
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:18,967
You're having problems
with money.

195
00:12:19,033 --> 00:12:21,233
This is the answer.
This is the solution.

196
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:23,367
Come on.

197
00:12:23,433 --> 00:12:26,267
Mom, please.

198
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:28,400
How can you say that?

199
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:32,800
You see, we don't know
what to do anymore.

200
00:12:32,867 --> 00:12:35,200
I just want to help.

201
00:12:37,267 --> 00:12:39,000
He's not even marrying you.

202
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:42,933
Give the child away.

203
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,900
What do you want
the people to think?

204
00:12:44,967 --> 00:12:46,300
You got pregnant
out of wedlock?

205
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:55,233
Mom, I don't care
what other people say!

206
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:57,867
Mom,

207
00:12:57,933 --> 00:12:59,933
you were there
when I had a miscarriage.

208
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
You saw how
I suffered, remember?

209
00:13:04,067 --> 00:13:07,800
I was crying
almost every day.

210
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:12,933
I've prayed for a long
time to have a child.

211
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:17,533
And now you want me to just give
her to someone I barely know?

212
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,133
Dear,

213
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:22,933
I'm just thinking
about what's best for Kayla.

214
00:13:25,233 --> 00:13:29,200
You can't even pay
for her medications.

215
00:13:29,267 --> 00:13:31,833
If I were you,
I would think this way.

216
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:33,667
I hope you would
think this way...

217
00:13:33,733 --> 00:13:37,133
if you put the child for
adoption, guaranteed,

218
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:39,467
she will have a better life.

219
00:13:39,533 --> 00:13:41,400
Won't you like that?

220
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:42,633
I don't want to.

221
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:44,333
No.

222
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:47,567
I won't give my child away.

223
00:13:47,633 --> 00:13:49,833
I told you so.

224
00:13:49,900 --> 00:13:53,433
If you had listened to me, and
gave Kayla for adoption,

225
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:55,533
this wouldn't have happened.

226
00:13:55,633 --> 00:13:57,367
She would've been alive.

227
00:13:58,767 --> 00:14:00,500
Mom.

228
00:14:00,567 --> 00:14:04,567
Why do you seem to blame us?

229
00:14:05,967 --> 00:14:07,767
You had your chance.

230
00:14:07,833 --> 00:14:09,367
But you rejected it.

231
00:14:09,433 --> 00:14:12,133
Mom, please stop.

232
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,133
Which is better?

233
00:14:15,533 --> 00:14:17,733
You give your child
up for adoption,

234
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,600
but you know she's alive.

235
00:14:19,667 --> 00:14:23,600
Or you keep her,
but just like what happened,

236
00:14:23,667 --> 00:14:25,067
she goes missing.

237
00:14:25,133 --> 00:14:27,800
Why do you talk like that?

238
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:30,867
Why don't you seem
to be a mother?

239
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:33,600
If I were a good mother,

240
00:14:33,667 --> 00:14:35,767
I would prioritize
my child's well-being.

241
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:41,200
Are you saying
I'm not a good mother?

242
00:14:48,633 --> 00:14:51,533
I didn't say that!

243
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:54,467
I just don't want to see
you suffer like that!

244
00:14:54,533 --> 00:14:56,367
And your child, too!

245
00:14:56,433 --> 00:14:59,700
So what if I have a hard time?

246
00:14:59,767 --> 00:15:02,733
Isn't it part of being a parent?
Isn't it?

247
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:06,000
But have you given
your child a good life?

248
00:15:06,067 --> 00:15:08,967
Have you saved Kayla?

249
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:10,400
Why mom?

250
00:15:10,467 --> 00:15:12,733
How about you?

251
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:15,567
Can you do that
to your own child?

252
00:15:15,633 --> 00:15:22,633
Can you give her away
to someone you don't know?

253
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:24,133
Can you do that?

254
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:28,400
If I have to,
and there's a chance, I will!

255
00:15:32,300 --> 00:15:36,067
If a wealthy family came and
wanted to adopt you,

256
00:15:36,167 --> 00:15:37,733
why wouldn't I say no?

257
00:15:49,933 --> 00:15:53,900
I have a lot
of shortcomings as a mother.

258
00:15:53,967 --> 00:15:56,567
I wasn't able to give
you a better life.

259
00:15:56,633 --> 00:15:59,133
You grew up without a father.

260
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:02,200
I deprived you
of a lot of things.

261
00:16:02,267 --> 00:16:05,733
So maybe I should have
given you up for adoption.

262
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:09,367
So I wouldn't have to see
you suffering like that.

263
00:16:11,733 --> 00:16:16,567
And if I've longed
for you, I would endure it!

264
00:16:16,633 --> 00:16:21,033
What matters is you're
living a good life.

265
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:43,000
Emma.

266
00:16:43,067 --> 00:16:44,267
Emma.

267
00:16:51,167 --> 00:16:52,033
Emma.

268
00:16:53,233 --> 00:16:55,300
Emma.

269
00:16:55,367 --> 00:16:58,367
What happened to our
child is so painful.

270
00:16:58,433 --> 00:17:02,267
But I don't want you to think
you failed as a mother.

271
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:05,500
Because you gave
our daughter so much more.

272
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:08,300
Even though we had nothing,

273
00:17:08,367 --> 00:17:10,233
we still did everything

274
00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:13,767
so our child could live longer.

275
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:16,200
Even though you weren't
by Baby Kayla's side,

276
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:18,700
when the landslide happened,

277
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:23,400
she knew you didn't fail
as a mother.

278
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:28,300
So, I'm telling you, Emma.

279
00:17:28,367 --> 00:17:30,167
Believe me.

280
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:33,667
You're a very good mother.

281
00:17:35,733 --> 00:17:38,133
You didn't fall short
as a mother.

282
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:41,133
Dear.

283
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:55,133
Thank you.

284
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:59,400
Dear about...

285
00:18:59,467 --> 00:19:01,067
what happened yesterday.

286
00:19:03,033 --> 00:19:05,733
I just want to say that...

287
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:09,533
I don't blame you
for what happened to Kayla.

288
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:15,367
I just don't want
to see you suffer.

289
00:19:15,433 --> 00:19:18,567
You and your child.

290
00:19:18,633 --> 00:19:21,233
But what do I know?

291
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:23,967
I made a lot of mistakes.

292
00:19:24,033 --> 00:19:26,500
I've been a mother
for a long time,

293
00:19:26,567 --> 00:19:29,267
but I'm still learning.

294
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:36,167
But I saw in you...

295
00:19:36,433 --> 00:19:41,133
that a mother can do everything
for her child.

296
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:43,333
That's not true, Mom.

297
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:50,967
I also fell short
as Kayla's mother.

298
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:02,300
I couldn't give her this book.

299
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:08,867
I couldn't even read
her a storybook.

300
00:20:11,467 --> 00:20:13,700
What kind of a mother am I?

301
00:20:36,067 --> 00:20:39,467
- Dear.
- I'm worthless.

302
00:20:39,533 --> 00:20:40,867
That's not true.

303
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:46,300
God knows all your suffering.

304
00:20:46,367 --> 00:20:51,600
So, you have to learn
to forgive yourself.

305
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:59,133
Stop crying, dear. Don't cry.

306
00:21:38,867 --> 00:21:40,033
Kayla?

307
00:21:46,167 --> 00:21:47,967
Kayla, my dear?

308
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:55,300
Kayla?

309
00:21:56,233 --> 00:21:59,067
Kayla, my dear, Mom's here.

310
00:22:01,833 --> 00:22:03,067
Kayla?

311
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,767
Kayla?

312
00:22:08,133 --> 00:22:09,767
Kayla?

313
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:11,867
Kayla?

314
00:22:11,933 --> 00:22:13,333
- Kayla?
- Emma!

315
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:16,800
Emma! Emma,
you were having a nightmare.

316
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:18,667
Dan, it's Kayla.

317
00:22:18,733 --> 00:22:21,200
She's asking for help.

318
00:22:21,267 --> 00:22:23,867
- Kayla's gone, Emma.
- Dan, she's in our house.

319
00:22:23,933 --> 00:22:27,100
She's in our old house!
She's asking for help.

320
00:22:27,167 --> 00:22:28,967
Let's go there.

321
00:22:29,033 --> 00:22:31,567
- Let's go to her now!
- Kayla's gone, Emma.

322
00:22:31,633 --> 00:22:34,600
You were just dreaming.
You were having a nightmare.

323
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:36,733
Why is this happening to us?

324
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:38,633
What did we do wrong?

325
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:41,267
Emma, I don't know. Maybe...

326
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:43,300
everything happens for a reason.

327
00:22:43,367 --> 00:22:45,000
That's why this is happening.

328
00:22:53,867 --> 00:22:55,533
That's enough.

329
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:56,933
Kayla's gone.

330
00:23:01,067 --> 00:23:02,300
Please stop.

331
00:23:22,267 --> 00:23:23,400
Dan.

332
00:23:23,467 --> 00:23:25,600
What are you doing
to Kayla's towel?

333
00:23:25,667 --> 00:23:27,133
I'll throw it away.

334
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:28,567
Dan!

335
00:23:28,633 --> 00:23:30,733
It belongs to our child.

336
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,900
I know. But...

337
00:23:32,967 --> 00:23:35,467
Emma, we have no use
for it anymore.

338
00:23:36,867 --> 00:23:38,433
Kayla's gone.

339
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:41,900
So, you think we won't find
our child anymore?

340
00:23:44,233 --> 00:23:46,800
It's been two weeks, Emma.

341
00:23:48,367 --> 00:23:51,433
We don't see any sign
of our child.

342
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:53,500
Those people who got buried
underneath the ground,

343
00:23:53,567 --> 00:23:55,300
they just let them be.

344
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,667
Maybe Emma...

345
00:23:57,733 --> 00:23:59,933
maybe it's time that
we also accept the truth.

346
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,167
Accept what?

347
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:06,967
That our child is already dead?

348
00:24:07,033 --> 00:24:08,900
- No.
- What's going on?

349
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:11,900
Why are you fighting?

350
00:24:11,967 --> 00:24:15,067
My husband, Mom.

351
00:24:15,133 --> 00:24:17,633
He wants to throw
Kayla's towel away.

352
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:19,967
He wants to erase
Kayla's memories.

353
00:24:20,033 --> 00:24:24,000
It's so easy for you
to forget our daughter!

354
00:24:24,067 --> 00:24:25,300
No! It's not like that!

355
00:24:25,367 --> 00:24:27,233
- That's not true!
- That's the truth!

356
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:28,900
No! That's not true!

357
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:32,700
Mom.

358
00:24:32,767 --> 00:24:35,133
I want to see my child so badly.

359
00:24:37,333 --> 00:24:40,167
If only I could give my life so
she could live again,

360
00:24:40,233 --> 00:24:41,333
I would do so!

361
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,867
But every time I see our
child's belongings,

362
00:24:48,533 --> 00:24:50,300
I get hurt.

363
00:24:50,367 --> 00:24:54,433
I'm suffering.
It's so painful, Emma!

364
00:24:58,067 --> 00:25:00,333
Because until now,
I still can't forgive myself!

365
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:03,567
It's my fault
that we lost our child!

366
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:14,267
It's my fault.

367
00:25:18,800 --> 00:25:21,167
It's my fault.

368
00:25:23,733 --> 00:25:29,000
I should have died
instead of our child, Emma.

369
00:25:29,067 --> 00:25:32,467
I wish it was me
who got buried.

370
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:43,700
I wish I could've done
something to save her.

371
00:25:43,767 --> 00:25:45,700
Dan, that's enough.

372
00:25:45,767 --> 00:25:49,267
I wish I could come
home for her, Emma.

373
00:25:49,333 --> 00:25:52,200
So that we're still together.

374
00:26:18,100 --> 00:26:20,033
It's me, your dad.

375
00:26:22,467 --> 00:26:25,667
We still can't accept
that you're gone.

376
00:26:26,833 --> 00:26:28,633
As your father,

377
00:26:29,933 --> 00:26:32,800
I know I must care for you

378
00:26:34,533 --> 00:26:36,100
and look after you.

379
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:40,033
But I couldn't even save you.

380
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:43,333
Because I was weak.

381
00:26:45,100 --> 00:26:47,667
I hope you can
forgive us, dear.

382
00:26:51,967 --> 00:26:53,267
Goodbye, my child.

383
00:26:55,533 --> 00:27:00,633
I'd prayed for you to come into
our lives for a long time.

384
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:02,467
So when we were in the hospital,

385
00:27:03,900 --> 00:27:07,133
all the tiredness and staying up
late didn't matter,

386
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:09,067
just to see you.

387
00:27:11,267 --> 00:27:13,600
But I don't understand.

388
00:27:13,667 --> 00:27:17,133
Why did we only have you
with us for a short while?

389
00:27:17,233 --> 00:27:19,033
Now,

390
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:22,233
I have to accept that...

391
00:27:22,300 --> 00:27:25,600
there is a big hole
in my heart.

392
00:27:26,767 --> 00:27:28,367
For the short time

393
00:27:29,900 --> 00:27:33,100
you were with us.

394
00:27:33,167 --> 00:27:35,333
I'm still grateful for you

395
00:27:36,667 --> 00:27:39,233
that you made me
feel like a mother

396
00:27:40,867 --> 00:27:42,233
My only wish is,

397
00:27:43,267 --> 00:27:45,167
wherever you are now,

398
00:27:46,233 --> 00:27:49,267
I hope you're in a good place.

399
00:28:31,633 --> 00:28:33,867
Hello, little darling.

400
00:28:35,100 --> 00:28:36,633
Hi.

401
00:28:55,700 --> 00:28:56,800
Emma,

402
00:28:56,900 --> 00:28:59,333
I have a favor to ask of you.

403
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:00,333
What is it?

404
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:03,333
Is it okay for you
to take care of my child?

405
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:06,067
Because I'm flying to Macau.

406
00:29:06,133 --> 00:29:09,500
Good morning, birthday girl!

407
00:29:09,567 --> 00:29:12,500
I can't believe it, dear.

408
00:29:12,567 --> 00:29:14,467
You're now 17.

409
00:29:14,533 --> 00:29:15,833
Actually...

410
00:29:15,900 --> 00:29:19,300
I've been waiting for my
birthday party for a long time.

411
00:29:19,367 --> 00:29:23,067
But drink your meds first.

412
00:29:23,133 --> 00:29:26,067
What is that child's illness?

413
00:29:26,133 --> 00:29:28,067
That puzzled me.

414
00:29:28,133 --> 00:29:31,567
Malou, I brought you here
to be a housekeeper,

415
00:29:31,667 --> 00:29:34,333
not a gossiper.

416
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:37,800
- Is that really necessary?
- Trust me, dear.

417
00:29:37,867 --> 00:29:39,500
Remember,

418
00:29:39,567 --> 00:29:40,833
I'm a doctor.
